    "body": "This does not prevent the vulnerability, I think? Someone can still create a large number of high-(legacy)sigops transactions, and the mining code will include them, resulting in a very small block.\n\nAFAIK the only workable solution is to treat transactions in the mempool as if their size was max(size, sigops \\* MAX_BLOCK_SIZE / MAX_SIGOPS).\n",
